The '''Central Illinois Railroad''' {{reporting mark|CIRY}} is a [[Class III railroad]] in [[Illinois]]. This switching railroad owns about 20 miles of trackage in [[Chicago, Illinois]]. The Central Illinois Railroad was established on [[November 23]], [[2000]] by leasing track from [[Burlington Northern and Santa Fe Railway]]. [[DOT Rail Services]] owns the Central Illinois Railroad.  


